          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "This school is good only if your child is good in her studies. I always wondered why this school always had 100%(or closer) SSC passing percentage. The principal keeps track of children who perform very poorly in their 9th exams. If the student fails the 9th class then they wont allow the child to repeat the class. Not even once! Instead they directly kick the child out of school. By eliminating/kicking out weak students they are able to maintain excellent SSC passing percentage. I am not sure if there  is any law that does not allow failed students to repeat a class, but this type of rule is not at all acceptable.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
